The paper deals with inferring players' values from their actions in repeated games, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on datasets from experiments, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning techniques (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper is related to econometrics (cs.EC) and social networks (cs.SI) as it deals with modeling and analyzing repeated games with controlled player values.
